x4freetext: Targets were prepared by evaporating a thin layer of
beryllium onto 10-microinch nickel foil. The targets
had thicknesses of between 25 and 50 keV to the
incident beam.
Ilford C-2 200-micron nuclear emulsions for
angular distributions of the proton groups leaving the
11B nucleus in its ground and 1-st excited states
A sliding seal chamber and CsI scintillation
detector for proton groups p0 - p6 at 4.5 MeV.
The error due to normalization. Absolute cross
sections were obtained by normalizing all measurements
to an absolute differential cross-section determination
made at 2.0 MeV.
CNPD: corrected 4-dig. year

x4freetext: Error from error bars ann digitizing.
The error bars include a uncertainty in the
determination of the solid angle, an estimated
uncertainty in the counting of the track statistical
uncertainties due to the number of track counted,
due to a small overlap in the pulse-height spectrum
between proton groups p2 and p3 or due to pulses caused
by other reaction products from the target which lay
in the same region of the pulse-height spectrum a
proton groups p4,5 and p6 (major portion of the
total uncertainty for these two groups).
